The paper discusses the development of a self-learning fuzzy cloud controller, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of fuzzy logic and Q-learning algorithms suggests that the paper also belongs to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The focus on runtime adaptation and learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
